description: From Latin past participle stem obstruct- (“blocked up”), from verb obstruere, from ob (“against”) + struere (“pile up, build”).

verbs.description: obstruct (third-person singular simple present obstructs, present participle obstructing, simple past and past participle obstructed)

entries.meaning: To block or fill (a passage) with obstacles or an obstacle. See synonyms at block.
To impede, retard, or interfere with; hinder.
To get in the way of so as to hide from sight.
